 {"id":"bd-n73h4","title":"Reject oversized ext4 inline-data inode sizes","description":"Fresh-eyes ext4 inline-data follow-up: read_ext4_inline_data caps reads by assembled inline_data.len(), so an inode whose i_size exceeds i_block + system.data capacity silently returns a short read despite the comment saying it pads. Inline-data ext4 files should fit in inline storage; reject this malformed metadata instead of truncating or zero-padding it.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cod-fs","created_at":"2026-04-27T08:59:37.740402051Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T09:04:27.057342881Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T09:04:27.055390923Z","close_reason":"Ext4 inline-data reads now reject i_size values larger than assembled inline capacity instead of silently short-reading or zero-padding malformed metadata; added focused oversized-capacity regression. Validation passed: focused ffs-core inline-data regressions, fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, workspace check, and workspace clippy.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-n8blq","title":"Conformance harness: build syscall-level conformance tests vs reference fs","description":"Apply /testing-conformance-harnesses skill. Build a conformance test that drives our fs through the same syscall sequences as a reference (Linux ext4 in tmpfs). Differential diff outputs per syscall (return value, errno, side effects). Cover: file lifecycle, directory ops, attribute ops, link semantics, mmap interaction, fsync semantics, mount/umount.","notes":"2026-04-26 cod-fs: extended syscall conformance matrix with reference/FUSE differential negative errno contracts for mkdir(EEXIST), unlink/rename(ENOENT), and rmdir(ENOTEMPTY); added reference-only regression guard. 2026-04-26 cod-fs: added fd metadata syscall coverage for fchmod, ftruncate, fstat, fsync, and path stat equivalence; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS, targeted reference probes, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: extended syscall differential harness with symlink fstatat/readlinkat/O_NOFOLLOW contracts and a reference regression guard; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, reference probes, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy; commit 9bd9141 pushed to main and mirrored to master. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: added truncate-extension zero-fill coverage to the syscall differential harness with reference guard; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, reference probe group, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy; commit 75ad9f8 pushed to main and mirrored to master. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: added open-unlink fd lifetime coverage to the syscall differential harness with reference guard; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, reference probe group, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy; commit efe814e pushed to main and mirrored to master. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: added op